_info.comment:
Test various examples to see if they are valid or invalid.
Implements
  EOF1V4750_0001 (Valid) EOF code containing single type section
  EOF1V4750_0002 (Valid) EOF code containing single type section and data section
  EOF1V4750_0003 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections
  EOF1V4750_0004 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections and data section
  EOF1V4750_0005 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections, no void I/O types
  EOF1V4750_0006 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections, no void I/O types, containing data section
  EOF1V4750_0007 (Valid) EOF code containing RETF as terminating instruction
  EOF1V4750_0008 (Valid) EOF code containing RETF as terminating instruction, containing data section
  EOF1V4750_0009 (Valid) EOF code containing the maximum number of code sections
  EOF1V4750_0010 (Valid) EOF code containing the maximum number of code sections and data section
  EOF1I4750_0001 (Invalid) EOF code missing mandatory type section
  EOF1I4750_0002 (Invalid) EOF code containing multiple type headers
  EOF1I4750_0003 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 1)
  EOF1I4750_0004 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 8 - 1 Code section)
  EOF1I4750_0005 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 8 - 3 Code sections)
  EOF1I4750_0006 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (1,0) (First section having a type different than (0,0))
  EOF1I4750_0007 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (0,1) (First section having a type different than (0,0))
  EOF1I4750_0008 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (2,3) (First section having a type different than (0,0))
  EOF1V4750_0011 (Invalid) EOF code containing too many code sections
  EOF1I4750_0009 (Invalid) EOF code containing CALLF to a non existing code section
  EOF1I4750_0010 (Invalid) EOF code containing truncated CALLF
  EOF1I4750_0011 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (JUMP)
  EOF1I4750_0012 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (JUMPI)
  EOF1I4750_0013 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (PC)
  EOF1I4750_0014 (Invalid) EOF code containing call to functions without required stack specified in type section
  EOF1I4750_0015 (Invalid) EOF code containing call to functions without required stack NOT specified in type section
  EOF1I4750_0016 (Invalid) EOF code containing function trying to return more items than specified in type section
  EOF1I4750_0017 (Invalid) EOF code containing function exceeding max stack items
